  "prompt": "What is Yelp?",
  "response": "Yelp is a popular online platform and mobile app that connects users with local businesses. Founded in 2004, Yelp allows users to search for businesses (such as restaurants, bars, salons, plumbers, and more) and read or write reviews about their experiences. Businesses are typically rated on a scale of one to five stars, and users can also upload photos and provide detailed feedback.\n\nKey features of Yelp include:\n\n1. **Business Listings**: Detailed information about local businesses, including hours, contact information, menus, and services offered.\n2. **User Reviews**: Crowdsourced reviews and ratings from customers who have used the business.\n3. **Photos**: Users and businesses can upload images to showcase their products, services, or ambiance.\n4. **Search and Filters**: Users can search for businesses by category, location, or keywords, and filter results by rating, price, and other criteria.\n5. **Yelp Elite Squad**: A community of active and trusted reviewers who are recognized for their contributions.\n6. **Business Tools**: Businesses can claim their Yelp profile, respond to reviews, and advertise on the platform to attract more customers.\n\nYelp is widely used by consumers to make informed decisions about where to eat, shop, or hire services, and by businesses to engage with customers and build their reputation.",
